{"questionId":"9076220","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Muons are created in the upper atmosphere of the Earth at an altitude of 10 km above the surface. The muons travel vertically down at a speed of 0.995<em>c </em>with respect to the Earth. When measured at rest the average lifetime of the muons is 2.1 μs.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate, according to the theory of special relativity, the time taken for a muon to reach the ground in the reference frame of the muon.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\gamma &nbsp;= 10\">\n  <mi>γ</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>10</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\Delta {t_0} = \">\n  <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{\\Delta t}}{\\gamma } = \\frac{{34}}{{10}} = \">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>γ</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>34</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong> 3.4<strong> «</strong><em>μs</em><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076220","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ1.b.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate, according to the theory of special relativity, the time taken for a muon to reach the ground in the reference frame of the muon.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)","A.2 – Lorentz t